</context>
<context>
	<score>0.46500197</score>
	<text>Inflation-indexed bonds (also known as inflation-linked bonds or colloquially as linkers ) are bonds where the principal is indexed to inflation . They are thus designed to cut out the inflation risk of an investment.</text>
</context>
